High-Grade Glioma Molecular Subtyping - Gene Expression

Chante Bethell and Jaclyn Taroni for ALSF CCDL

2020

This notebook prepares gene expression data for the purposes of subtyping HGG samples (AlexsLemonade/OpenPBTA-analysis#249).

Usage

This notebook is intended to be run via the command line from the top directory of the repository as follows:

Rscript -e "rmarkdown::render('analyses/molecular-subtyping-HGG/06-HGG-molecular-subtyping-gene-expression.Rmd', clean = TRUE)"

Set up

Libraries and Functions

library(tidyverse)

# Detect the ".git" folder -- this will in the project root directory.

  file.path(root_dir, "analyses", "molecular-subtyping-HGG", "hgg-subset")

Read in Files

The gene expression files were generated by filtering z-scored expression data (handling polyA selection and stranded expression files separately) for the purpose of subtyping HGG samples.

# Read in subsetted polyA expression data
polya_expression_df <-
  read_rds(file.path(input_dir, "hgg_zscored_expression.polya.RDS"))

# Read in subsetted stranded expression data
stranded_expression_df <-
  read_rds(file.path(input_dir, "hgg_zscored_expression.stranded.RDS"))

Output Files

# File path to cleaned polyA expression output
polya_output_file <- file.path(results_dir, "HGG_cleaned_expression.polya.tsv")

# File path to cleaned stranded expression output
stranded_output_file <-
  file.path(results_dir, "HGG_cleaned_expression.stranded.tsv")

Which genes expression values are we interested in?

There are three genes of interest according to AlexsLemonade/OpenPBTA-analysis#249. Specifically:

  • OLIG2 and FOXG1 should be highly expressed in the IDH mutant HGG subtype.
  • TP73-AS1 methylation and downregulation cooccur with TP53 mutations in the IDH mutant subtype.

Filter and Wrangle Expression Data

filter_wrangle_expression <-
  function(cleaned_expression, output_file_path) {
    # Given an expression data.frame filtered to include only samples that meet
    # the HGG classification criteria, select the genes of interest. It displays
    # and writes the cleaned and filtered expression table to the given output
    # file path.
    
    filtered_expression <- cleaned_expression %>%
      as.data.frame() %>%
      rownames_to_column("Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID") %>%
      select(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID,
             FOXG1_expression_zscore = FOXG1,
             OLIG2_expression_zscore = OLIG2,
             TP73_AS1_expression_zscore = `TP73-AS1`) %>%
      distinct()
    
    # Save expression data to file
    write_tsv(filtered_expression, output_file_path)
    
    # Display `filtered_expression`
    filtered_expression
  }

# Run `filter_wrangle_expression` on poly-A cleaned expression data
filter_wrangle_expression(polya_expression_df , polya_output_file)

# Run `filter_wrangle_expression` on stranded cleaned expression data 
filter_wrangle_expression(stranded_expression_df , stranded_output_file)

Density Plots

plot_expression_density <- function(expression_file) {
  # Given the cleaned expression file from the previous chunck, generate a
  # density plot for each of the three genes of interest. This function returns
  # three density plots(one per gene).
  
  # Read in file
  expression_df <- read_tsv(expression_file)
  
  # Plot FOXG1 expression data and save plot
  FOXG1_expression_density_plot <-
    ggplot(expression_df,
           aes(FOXG1_expression_zscore)) +
    geom_density(alpha = 0.1) +
    theme_classic()
  
  # Plot OLIG2 expression data and save plot
  OLIG2_expression_density_plot <-
    ggplot(expression_df,
           aes(OLIG2_expression_zscore)) +
    geom_density(alpha = 0.1) +
    theme_classic()
  
  # Plot TP73-AS1 expression data and save plot
  TP73_AS1_expression_density_plot <-
    ggplot(expression_df,
           aes(TP73_AS1_expression_zscore)) +
    geom_density(alpha = 0.1) +
    theme_classic()
  
  #Display plots
  list(
    FOXG1_expression_density_plot,
    OLIG2_expression_density_plot,
    TP73_AS1_expression_density_plot
  )
}

# Run `plot_expression_density` on cleaned polyA data
plot_expression_density(polya_output_file)
